3. Customer
Add Customer
POST http://localhost:8080/api/customers
Valid JSON Body: (using existing ids for city, state, country, occupation)

{
  "firstName": "Arun",
  "lastName": "Kumar",
  "gender": "M",
  "dob": "1995-03-10",
  "mobileNumber": "9876543210",
  "cityId": 1,
  "stateId": 1,
  "countryId": 1,
  "occupationId": 1
}


‚ùå Add Customer (Empty firstName)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/customers
Invalid JSON Body:

{
  "firstName": "",
  "lastName": "Kumar",
  "gender": "M",
  "dob": "1995-03-10",
  "mobileNumber": "9876543210",
  "cityId": 1,
  "stateId": 1,
  "countryId": 1,
  "occupationId": 1
}
Expected Error: Error: First name is required.

Get All Customers
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers

Get Customer by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/1